{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NyXnBNF9uzAGMtEQfdKFdk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tname: lesson-docker-stale-lockfile-cache\n3\tdescription: Deploy failures from a stale lockfile cached in a Docker build layer — clear the build cache\n4\tmetadata: \n5\t  node_type: memory\n6\t  type: project\n7\t  originSessionId: ff5b9bfa-d8b8-4804-9b23-4b187014e85b\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tA deploy kept failing because the Dockerfile was caching a stale lockfile in a build layer. Clearing the Docker build cache fixed it.\n11\t\n12\t**Why:** Docker layer caching can hold an old lockfile even after the source lockfile changes, so dependency installs run against stale versions. The failure looks like a code/dependency problem, not a caching one.\n13\t\n14\t**How to apply:** When a deploy fails on dependencies but the lockfile looks correct locally, suspect a cached build layer early. Rebuild with the build cache cleared (e.g. `docker build --no-cache`) before deeper debugging.\n15\t\n16\tRelated: [[lesson-staging-debug-swallows-errors]] — both are cases where the real cause is a layer/flag between you and the code, not the code itself.\n17\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec5f2c1e-e366-4f44-8af4-72ac7bd6ba9a","uuid":"9295a628-251e-4628-adba-338be01a39f9","timestamp":"2026-07-12T02:08:24.330Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-claude-501--Users-davidlayson-83ee2e2e-2641-4713-b439-5260ae8e5d1e-scratchpad/memory/lesson-docker-stale-lockfile-cache.md","content":"---\nname: lesson-docker-stale-lockfile-cache\ndescription: Deploy failures from a stale lockfile cached in a Docker build layer — clear the build cache\nmetadata: \n  node_type: memory\n  type: project\n  originSessionId: ff5b9bfa-d8b8-4804-9b23-4b187014e85b\n---\n\nA deploy kept failing because the Dockerfile was caching a stale lockfile in a build layer. Clearing the Docker build cache fixed it.\n\n**Why:** Docker layer caching can hold an old lockfile even after the source lockfile changes, so dependency installs run against stale versions. The failure looks like a code/dependency problem, not a caching one.\n\n**How to apply:** When a deploy fails on dependencies but the lockfile looks correct locally, suspect a cached build layer early. Rebuild with the build cache cleared (e.g. `docker build --no-cache`) before deeper debugging.\n\nRelated: [[lesson-staging-debug-swallows-errors]] — both are cases where the real cause is a layer/flag between you and the code, not the code itself.\n","numLines":17,"startLine":1,"totalLines":17}}}
